    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Invest in the Dot-Orgs</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Dr Sue Ann Brenner letter disputes Andy Borowitz's May 9 Op-Ed article on switch by investors from dot-coms to dot-orgs (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Andy Borowitz (''The Nonprofit Motive,'' Op-Ed, May 9) jokes that investors should switch from dot-coms to dot-orgs like audubon.org and sierraclub.org.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Andy Borowitz (''The Nonprofit Motive,'' Op-Ed, May 9) jokes that investors should switch from dot-coms to dot-orgs like audubon.org and sierraclub.org.</p>
        <p>But investing in dot-orgs really is a good idea. Think about it: Instead of wringing your fingers the next time the stock market crashes, you can put some of your dollars to work cleaning up America's air and water, improving our environment and our quality of life. Not a bad investment.</p>
        <p>SUE ANNE BRENNER, M.D.  Atlanta, May 9, 2000</p>
      </block>
